english_definitions: to be able to possess (hold, get, etc.)
to be pampered (spoiled, doted upon, etc.)
to endure (the tests of time, the elements, etc.)
to bring out from where it belongs
large oblong chest (for clothing, personal effects, etc.)

english_definitions: to bring to (a state: tied game, vote, trial, etc.)
distinctive characteristic (of a person, work, etc.)
to hold out (e.g. against an attack)
parent or someone with children on the way (esp. an expecting mother)
to happen to have on hand or in stock
to be homeroom teacher for the same class multiple years in a row
to move up with one's class
to be too much for one
to not know what to do with
holding two or more positions concurrently
to turn a deaf ear to
inspection of personal belongings (e.g. before entering a venue)
work, items, etc. carried over from earlier
what you ate the day before (and is still being digested)

japanese.reading: えんのしたのちからもち

english_definitions: person who does a thankless task
someone who is always following around someone of high rank
someone who carries a bag for someone
to have two things (at the same time) (e.g. good and bad points)
to also have something (in addition to something else)
to have a family (e.g. wife or husband and children)
to let someone have the credit for (a success)
to let someone else carry the flowers
to encourage someone to expect something
